					<head>Collection of marriage and divorce contracts</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85072105" rend="visible">
						<summary>A marriage contract (ketubah) and two divorce contracts (get).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="5v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ketubot ve-geṭ</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">כתובות וגט</title>
							<note>
								<p>A: Paper fragment recording the appointment of delegates charged with the delivery of a get to a woman about to be divorced. Dated <date calendar="Hebrew">5514</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1754</date>). (see fols. 1r-1v on digital surrogate)</p>
								<p>B: A marriage contract on parchment, between Shemu᾿el ben Avraham and Raḥel bat David, signed in <name type="place">Damavand</name>, <date calendar="Hebrew">5529</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1769</date>). (see fols. 2r-3v on digital surrogate)</p>
								<p>C: A divorce document on paper, by which Leṿi ben Numdar (?) divorces Śarah ben Benyamin. The date is <date calendar="Hebrew">5514</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1754</date>). (see fols. 4r-5v on digital surrogate)</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
